==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uptake
<hw>Up*take"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To take into the
hand; to take up; to help.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.
Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uptake</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uptake
<hw>Up"take`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Steam
Boilers)</fld>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The pipe leading upward from the smoke box of a
steam boiler to the chimney, or smokestack; a flue leading
upward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Understanding; apprehension.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uptear</ent>⟦br⟧
